-- Europe shares steady at open; H&M drops after results
-- By Blaise Robinson
-- Thu Sep 25, 2014 03:08AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, Sept 25 (Reuters) - European shares were steady in early trading on Thursday, halting the previous session's rebound, while Hennes & Mauritz <HMb.ST> lost ground after saying sales had slowed in September.

At 0703 GMT, the FTSEurofirst 300 <.FTEU3> index of top European shares was up 0.02 percent at 1,386.10 points, after gaining 0.8 percent on Wednesday.